message.content:
In /Users/ryanvasquez/reading-tracker, do a search-and-replace across all component files to update modal button styles for a Spotify-premium redesign.

The changes to make using sed:

1. In all .tsx files under /components, replace the old blue rgba shadow on primary buttons with indigo:
   - `shadow-[0_0_12px_rgba(8,116,224,0.2)]` → `shadow-[0_0_16px_rgba(79,70,229,0.25)]`
   - `shadow-[0_0_12px_rgba(8,116,224,0.3)]` → `shadow-[0_0_16px_rgba(79,70,229,0.3)]`

2. In all .tsx files under /components, change primary button shapes from rounded-lg to rounded-full ONLY on lines that contain both `bg-ripple-6` (primary buttons) and `rounded-lg`:

3. In app/page.tsx, replace the button shadows too.

Run these commands:
```bash
# Update shadow rgba in components (blue → indigo)
find /Users/ryanvasquez/reading-tracker/components -name "*.tsx" -exec sed -i '' 's/shadow-\[0_0_12px_rgba(8,116,224,0\.2)\]/shadow-[0_0_16px_rgba(79,70,229,0.25)]/g' {} \;
find /Users/ryanvasquez/reading-tracker/components -name "*.tsx" -exec sed -i '' 's/shadow-\[0_0_12px_rgba(8,116,224,0\.3)\]/shadow-[0_0_16px_rgba(79,70,229,0.3)]/g' {} \;

# Update in app files too
find /Users/ryanvasquez/reading-tracker/app -name "*.tsx" -exec sed -i '' 's/shadow-\[0_0_12px_rgba(8,116,224,0\.2)\]/shadow-[0_0_16px_rgba(79,70,229,0.25)]/g' {} \;
find /Users/ryanvasquez/reading-tracker/app -name "*.tsx" -exec sed -i '' 's/shadow-\[0_0_12px_rgba(8,116,224,0\.3)\]/shadow-[0_0_16px_rgba(79,70,229,0.3)]/g' {} \;
find /Users/ryanvasquez/reading-tracker/app -name "*.tsx" -exec sed -i '' 's/shadow-\[0_0_16px_rgba(8,116,224,0\.4)\]/shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(79,70,229,0.35)]/g' {} \;

# Update progress bar glow  
find /Users/ryanvasquez/reading-tracker/app -name "*.tsx" -exec sed -i '' 's/shadow-\[0_0_6px_rgba(16,144,255,0\.4)\]/shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(99,102,241,0.5)]/g' {} \;
find /Users/ryanvasquez/reading-tracker/components -name "*.tsx" -exec sed -i '' 's/shadow-\[0_0_6px_rgba(16,144,255,0\.4)\]/shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(99,102,241,0.5)]/g' {} \;
```

Run all these commands and output the results showing what changed.
